1
00:00:10,040 --> 00:00:11,960
(Previously)
Since when did we hire this baker?

2
00:00:12,160 --> 00:00:13,560
Are you a "hit and run" guy?

3
00:00:13,720 --> 00:00:15,120
It was just a "friends with benefits" thing.

4
00:00:15,160 --> 00:00:16,960
- Are you hungry?
- Huh? Hungry for what?

5
00:00:17,080 --> 00:00:18,760
Whoa, easy! You'll get drunk.

6
00:00:18,960 --> 00:00:20,520
I can handle this much.

7
00:00:23,600 --> 00:00:25,960
And finally...

8
00:00:26,960 --> 00:00:28,280
200 drinks.

9
00:00:31,320 --> 00:00:33,080
I don't just sleep with anyone.

10
00:00:33,120 --> 00:00:35,120
From now on, you have to call me...

11
00:00:35,160 --> 00:00:36,320
P'Doc.

12
00:00:36,960 --> 00:00:38,120
Nong Sailom.

13
00:00:38,480 --> 00:00:39,640
Okay, P'Doc.

14
00:01:39,800 --> 00:01:44,800
"Love Like a Bike"
(Episode 3)

15
00:01:47,840 --> 00:01:49,040
Here's a receipt.

16
00:01:49,640 --> 00:01:51,320
The cakes are good,

17
00:01:51,320 --> 00:01:53,040
but do you have less sweet ones?

18
00:01:53,080 --> 00:01:56,280
Do you have keto or stevia cakes?

19
00:01:56,280 --> 00:01:59,880
I'm watching my weight but can't resist.

20
00:02:00,600 --> 00:02:03,160
We don't have those yet,

21
00:02:03,320 --> 00:02:05,800
but I'll let you know as soon as we do.

22
00:02:06,160 --> 00:02:07,400
Thank you.

23
00:02:07,440 --> 00:02:08,520
You're welcome.

24
00:02:10,960 --> 00:02:12,000
Auntie Phailin,

25
00:02:12,960 --> 00:02:15,720
should I try making less sweet cakes?

26
00:02:16,280 --> 00:02:18,520
Maybe we can use stevia instead of sugar

27
00:02:18,880 --> 00:02:20,760
for health-conscious customers.

28
00:02:21,880 --> 00:02:22,960
Of course.

29
00:02:23,200 --> 00:02:25,880
I'll give you the
leeway to try it out.

30
00:02:26,440 --> 00:02:27,360
Thank you.

31
00:02:56,360 --> 00:02:57,560
That'll do.

32
00:03:06,040 --> 00:03:07,080
What are you baking?

33
00:03:08,080 --> 00:03:09,200
Banana cakes.

34
00:03:12,680 --> 00:03:13,600
What?

35
00:03:14,160 --> 00:03:15,960
Who kicked your ass this time?

36
00:03:16,200 --> 00:03:16,920
Piss off.

37
00:03:30,040 --> 00:03:31,080
Dindin,

38
00:03:31,400 --> 00:03:33,280
why the hell does this taste crappy?!

39
00:03:35,480 --> 00:03:37,200
Did you change my recipe?

40
00:03:37,680 --> 00:03:40,600
No, no. It's the same one.

41
00:03:40,920 --> 00:03:41,880
I just cut down the sugar

42
00:03:41,920 --> 00:03:43,160
and used stevia instead.

43
00:03:43,240 --> 00:03:44,440
What for?!

44
00:03:44,440 --> 00:03:46,800
You'd rather spend
your time restocking the display!

45
00:03:47,320 --> 00:03:49,600
Hey, I'm doing what you said now.

46
00:03:49,720 --> 00:03:51,440
Always arguing with me, huh?

47
00:03:51,960 --> 00:03:53,320
Stop! Enough of this!

48
00:03:53,360 --> 00:03:55,240
Hey, hey! What are you doing?!

49
00:03:55,360 --> 00:03:56,480
Throw them away!

50
00:03:56,520 --> 00:03:57,480
Why?

51
00:03:58,440 --> 00:04:00,160
It's not up to standard!

52
00:04:00,480 --> 00:04:01,600
The recipe is still a work in progress.

53
00:04:01,640 --> 00:04:02,920
Just chill out.

54
00:04:05,960 --> 00:04:07,960
My café is not a lab,

55
00:04:08,760 --> 00:04:11,240
where you can experiment
whenever you feel like it!

56
00:04:12,120 --> 00:04:13,680
I talked to Auntie Phailin.

57
00:04:13,840 --> 00:04:15,240
Go talk to her yourself.

58
00:04:15,320 --> 00:04:17,360
Don't hide behind my mom.

59
00:04:17,880 --> 00:04:19,640
When will you stop picking on me?

60
00:04:20,640 --> 00:04:21,880
I'm being honest!

61
00:04:22,740 --> 00:04:24,380
Your banana cake is trash!

62
00:04:24,720 --> 00:04:25,840
That's it!

63
00:04:27,360 --> 00:04:29,800
Stop fighting! Dindin! Stop!

64
00:04:30,640 --> 00:04:33,520
Why can't you two talk like adults?!

65
00:04:38,160 --> 00:04:39,560
I'm sorry, Auntie Phailin.

66
00:04:40,560 --> 00:04:42,760
Can't you two just keep this civil?!

67
00:04:42,960 --> 00:04:44,520
About the cakes,

68
00:04:44,640 --> 00:04:46,960
I allowed Dindin to do it!

69
00:04:47,160 --> 00:04:51,000
I don't know what's
going on between you two,

70
00:04:51,520 --> 00:04:52,840
but while you're at work,

71
00:04:53,360 --> 00:04:55,320
can you please talk nicely?

72
00:05:01,400 --> 00:05:03,720
Tawan! Tawan!

73
00:05:09,960 --> 00:05:11,400
Keep doing them.

74
00:05:11,440 --> 00:05:12,400
Yes.

75
00:05:22,443 --> 00:05:24,316
- I'm winning now!
- Ouch!

76
00:05:25,400 --> 00:05:26,480
P'Doc!

77
00:05:26,880 --> 00:05:28,440
Come play in the water with me!

78
00:05:29,920 --> 00:05:30,800
Whose clip is that?

79
00:05:31,720 --> 00:05:33,240
Was that your "P'Doc?"

80
00:05:33,760 --> 00:05:35,480
How the heck do you know?

81
00:05:35,760 --> 00:05:37,440
Well, I heard it.

82
00:05:37,800 --> 00:05:39,280
How far have you guys gone?

83
00:05:39,960 --> 00:05:42,240
We're… just talking.

84
00:05:45,960 --> 00:05:46,760
Hey,

85
00:05:47,360 --> 00:05:50,000
do you know what he feels about me?

86
00:05:50,880 --> 00:05:52,000
Why?

87
00:05:52,600 --> 00:05:56,800
He told me "I'm cute."

88
00:05:58,240 --> 00:05:59,800
Does he say that to anyone?

89
00:06:00,360 --> 00:06:01,320
You think so?

90
00:06:01,760 --> 00:06:05,400
I doubt he tells everyone they're cute.

91
00:06:05,800 --> 00:06:08,200
Hey, he's a psychiatrist.

92
00:06:08,240 --> 00:06:10,280
He knows what people want to hear.

93
00:06:10,520 --> 00:06:13,240
Still, the Doctor is a busy guy.

94
00:06:13,280 --> 00:06:17,640
But he still invited you to dinner
and to talk. I think he's into you.

95
00:06:17,640 --> 00:06:20,200
Don't give him false hope, Lemon.

96
00:06:20,320 --> 00:06:21,760
Maybe psychiatrists have a way…

97
00:06:22,200 --> 00:06:25,520
to play mind games?
Have you guys even touched yet?

98
00:06:28,760 --> 00:06:30,240
What the hell is wrong with you?!

99
00:06:30,280 --> 00:06:31,800
Hey, I'm saying the truth.

100
00:06:31,960 --> 00:06:35,160
Alright! Stop rubbing it in!

101
00:06:35,880 --> 00:06:37,800
I won't text him.

102
00:06:45,520 --> 00:06:47,920
Who texted you? Was that the Doctor?

103
00:06:53,240 --> 00:07:00,480
"Are you free tomorrow? I'd love
to show you around Pattaya again."

104
00:07:00,640 --> 00:07:02,360
There! He likes you!

105
00:07:03,000 --> 00:07:04,560
He's just being polite.

106
00:07:15,600 --> 00:07:17,320
(Wanna call?)

107
00:07:24,000 --> 00:07:25,120
Get out!

108
00:07:25,240 --> 00:07:27,560
Where are your manners?

109
00:07:27,680 --> 00:07:28,960
Oh, you...

110
00:07:29,560 --> 00:07:30,920
Come on, let's go.

111
00:07:32,000 --> 00:07:32,920
Move it.

112
00:07:42,240 --> 00:07:44,760
Did you enjoy our bike ride?

113
00:07:45,160 --> 00:07:48,440
I did, P'Doc. I felt like…

114
00:07:49,080 --> 00:07:51,160
I got to see the real Pattaya.

115
00:07:51,280 --> 00:07:53,000
Since you've been back from the US,

116
00:07:53,025 --> 00:07:54,745
have you been
anywhere with your friends?

117
00:07:55,320 --> 00:08:01,360
Not really. My friends are gamers,
and I'm not a fan of crowded places.

118
00:08:01,680 --> 00:08:04,000
And what are you doing right now?

119
00:08:04,880 --> 00:08:06,640
Packing my things.

120
00:08:07,720 --> 00:08:11,600
I understand. I've been through
some tough times myself.

121
00:08:12,400 --> 00:08:14,880
But we'll get through it,
one way or another.

122
00:08:17,680 --> 00:08:20,320
Are all psychiatrists
such positive thinkers?

123
00:08:29,600 --> 00:08:30,480
P'Doc.

124
00:08:32,400 --> 00:08:33,280
P'Doc.

125
00:08:41,640 --> 00:08:42,560
P'Doc?

126
00:08:43,480 --> 00:08:44,320
P'Doc.

127
00:08:45,960 --> 00:08:46,560
Yes?

128
00:08:48,480 --> 00:08:49,480
I'm sorry.

129
00:08:50,480 --> 00:08:52,240
Are you okay?

130
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:55,120
I'm fine.

131
00:08:55,920 --> 00:08:57,680
I was lost in some old memories.

132
00:08:58,760 --> 00:09:01,360
And… where will you take me tomorrow?

133
00:09:03,720 --> 00:09:04,760
I'm not telling.

134
00:09:05,560 --> 00:09:06,880
It's a surprise.

135
00:09:09,000 --> 00:09:12,360
Alright, see you then.

136
00:09:12,840 --> 00:09:14,000
Bye bye.

137
00:09:16,440 --> 00:09:18,920
Dude, he's stringing you along.

138
00:09:19,120 --> 00:09:21,280
Just ask him if he's seeing anyone.

139
00:09:21,360 --> 00:09:22,320
Are you nuts?

140
00:09:22,880 --> 00:09:25,440
Yes, make things clear
so he stops being so vague.

141
00:10:09,080 --> 00:10:11,480
I haven't gone cycling with
my family for a long time.

142
00:10:12,440 --> 00:10:13,400
Why?

143
00:10:15,000 --> 00:10:15,560
Well…

144
00:10:16,960 --> 00:10:18,760
I usually went cycling with my family.

145
00:10:19,960 --> 00:10:24,160
But as everyone grew up
and started working,

146
00:10:25,440 --> 00:10:26,880
we haven't really done it lately.

147
00:10:30,040 --> 00:10:33,760
Since I came back,
I haven't met my dad too.

148
00:10:34,920 --> 00:10:40,040
Even though he's family, everyone
has their own life. Right, P'Doc?

149
00:10:45,720 --> 00:10:48,160
The whole city view is beautiful.

150
00:11:02,360 --> 00:11:04,440
It would be even better with a lover.

151
00:11:07,200 --> 00:11:08,800
Bring your girlfriend next time.

152
00:11:09,720 --> 00:11:11,920
Are you crazy?! I don't have one!

153
00:11:12,280 --> 00:11:14,680
I can't even let people touch me.

154
00:11:17,640 --> 00:11:18,800
And...

155
00:11:19,240 --> 00:11:20,280
what about you?

156
00:11:21,560 --> 00:11:22,800
Do you have one?

157
00:11:25,840 --> 00:11:27,000
I just broke up with her.

158
00:11:31,920 --> 00:11:33,320
I'm sorry about that.

159
00:11:34,440 --> 00:11:35,640
That's okay.

160
00:11:36,320 --> 00:11:37,600
I'm already moving on.

161
00:11:38,800 --> 00:11:40,160
That's kinda quick.

162
00:11:43,440 --> 00:11:45,120
Why did you two break up?

163
00:11:51,520 --> 00:11:52,920
I proposed to her.

164
00:11:56,560 --> 00:11:58,840
And she said she would work in Vietnam.

165
00:12:00,600 --> 00:12:01,920
So, she turned me me.

166
00:12:04,880 --> 00:12:06,680
I'm not sure if she…

167
00:12:07,160 --> 00:12:12,680
turned me down because of her work
or if we just weren't meant to be.

168
00:12:13,680 --> 00:12:15,160
I think…

169
00:12:15,840 --> 00:12:18,040
she didn't want you to wait for her.

170
00:12:18,760 --> 00:12:20,120
That's why.

171
00:12:23,880 --> 00:12:24,880
I guess so.

172
00:12:28,520 --> 00:12:29,520
What about you?

173
00:12:30,000 --> 00:12:31,440
Never had a girlfriend?

174
00:12:35,560 --> 00:12:36,880
Yes, I haven't!

175
00:12:37,920 --> 00:12:39,640
I've never had one.

176
00:12:42,480 --> 00:12:44,040
With my conditions,

177
00:12:45,040 --> 00:12:46,800
I'm scared that people won't…

178
00:12:49,680 --> 00:12:51,320
accept what I have.

179
00:12:54,600 --> 00:12:57,400
Sailom, It's okay to be scared.

180
00:12:58,160 --> 00:12:59,800
There's nothing wrong with that.

181
00:13:00,840 --> 00:13:03,240
Sometimes, it's better to be scared.

182
00:13:05,240 --> 00:13:07,800
Fear just makes you more careful

183
00:13:09,200 --> 00:13:11,520
about starting a relationship.

184
00:13:12,200 --> 00:13:14,320
Do you really think that way?

185
00:13:15,760 --> 00:13:16,600
Yes.

186
00:13:39,240 --> 00:13:44,160
It would be awesome… if more people
go cycling with us. We wouldn't be lonely.

187
00:13:47,896 --> 00:13:49,320
How about we start a trip?

188
00:14:01,560 --> 00:14:05,800
Okay, now we'll start drink bidding!

189
00:14:06,400 --> 00:14:07,760
Number 69, 60 drinks!

190
00:14:07,800 --> 00:14:10,840
Oh, wow! Our Sky gets 60 drinks...

191
00:14:10,840 --> 00:14:11,480
80.

192
00:14:11,520 --> 00:14:14,160
80 drinks! Going once...

193
00:14:14,160 --> 00:14:15,520
200 drinks!

194
00:14:15,520 --> 00:14:18,200
And here's 200 drinks! Going once...

195
00:14:18,240 --> 00:14:21,360
- 210!
- 210 drinks! Going once...

196
00:14:21,400 --> 00:14:24,800
- Make it 299!
- 299! Going once!

197
00:14:24,840 --> 00:14:26,280
Twice...

198
00:14:26,320 --> 00:14:27,280
350!

199
00:14:27,280 --> 00:14:31,160
350 drinks! Going once… twice...

200
00:14:31,200 --> 00:14:32,440
355!

201
00:14:32,440 --> 00:14:33,920
355 drinks...

202
00:14:33,960 --> 00:14:37,840
- Make it 400!
- 400! Now, it's 400! Any higher bids?

203
00:14:37,880 --> 00:14:40,040
Going once… twice…

204
00:14:40,080 --> 00:14:44,080
and SOLD! Off you go to the table, Sky!

205
00:14:44,080 --> 00:14:46,840
Now, he's off the floor!

206
00:14:47,960 --> 00:14:49,760
Is all this really necessary?

207
00:14:49,800 --> 00:14:51,360
For taking me back to my room.

208
00:14:52,200 --> 00:14:54,360
Did you really have to
compete with P'Man that much?

209
00:14:54,960 --> 00:14:57,160
I don't like people touching what's mine.

210
00:15:03,960 --> 00:15:07,160
Does this mean… I'm yours?

211
00:15:08,040 --> 00:15:11,480
It means… I just want you
to stay by my side.

212
00:15:29,400 --> 00:15:30,840
Your reward.

213
00:15:39,160 --> 00:15:40,440
Surprise!

214
00:15:40,680 --> 00:15:41,920
Wow!

215
00:15:44,720 --> 00:15:48,080
Oh!

216
00:15:49,360 --> 00:15:50,800
What is this?!

217
00:15:51,160 --> 00:15:54,520
The money garland for
the four-kid best mom.

218
00:15:54,560 --> 00:15:57,760
Oh, does it have to be this grand?

219
00:15:58,200 --> 00:15:59,960
Is this a Songkran day?

220
00:16:00,000 --> 00:16:02,400
Actually, I just got my commissions.

221
00:16:02,440 --> 00:16:07,680
I've been saving up for 15 days
to help you with the shop's rent.

222
00:16:08,080 --> 00:16:10,480
So nice of you. Thank you.

223
00:16:10,520 --> 00:16:11,840
Let me hug you.

224
00:16:14,640 --> 00:16:16,080
So refreshing.

225
00:16:16,120 --> 00:16:17,720
Now, you're the favorite son.

226
00:16:17,760 --> 00:16:19,560
Can I be her favorite one sometimes?

227
00:16:19,600 --> 00:16:23,200
I'm always back home late
and have to work at night.

228
00:16:23,240 --> 00:16:25,680
Unlike you, you're always with her.

229
00:16:26,400 --> 00:16:27,880
That was a sarcastic kiss.

230
00:16:28,320 --> 00:16:31,680
If Sky is your favorite son,
what about me?!

231
00:16:31,720 --> 00:16:34,360
Aww.

232
00:16:34,400 --> 00:16:36,880
I love you all equally.

233
00:16:41,000 --> 00:16:42,960
- Oh, Sky.
- Yes?

234
00:16:43,000 --> 00:16:45,240
Don't forget to rest.

235
00:16:45,560 --> 00:16:49,280
And don't drink too much booze,
or you'll get a hard liver.

236
00:16:49,320 --> 00:16:50,440
Alright.

237
00:16:50,440 --> 00:16:51,560
Yep, the favorite son.

238
00:16:52,000 --> 00:16:54,680
Now, your mom lectures you.

239
00:16:54,720 --> 00:16:58,960
And you. You're not a host,
but you drink day and night.

240
00:16:58,960 --> 00:16:59,960
(Keep lecturing him, Mom.)

241
00:17:00,200 --> 00:17:01,640
Didn't you lecture him?

242
00:17:02,160 --> 00:17:03,760
Why does it come back to me?

243
00:17:05,920 --> 00:17:07,400
How do I unwrap these?

244
00:17:07,680 --> 00:17:12,120
You want to unwrap them? It took me
all day to make the garland this big!

245
00:17:12,160 --> 00:17:16,640
I need to use the money.
And look, I've turned into a lizard!

246
00:17:16,840 --> 00:17:18,600
I'll help you unwrap them.

247
00:17:18,600 --> 00:17:20,200
If I help, can I have a share?

248
00:17:20,240 --> 00:17:22,600
Hey, stop right there. No.

249
00:17:22,640 --> 00:17:24,840
- Can I have some?
- No way! You can't!

250
00:17:28,360 --> 00:17:29,080
What?

251
00:17:29,680 --> 00:17:31,160
"A Heart-Healing Trip."

252
00:17:31,160 --> 00:17:35,160
Just checking in to see who's up
for a cycling trip to heal the soul.

253
00:17:36,080 --> 00:17:37,360
What's this, bro?

254
00:17:37,680 --> 00:17:39,120
A cycling trip.

255
00:17:39,240 --> 00:17:40,400
A cycling trip?

256
00:17:40,680 --> 00:17:41,400
Yep.

257
00:17:41,440 --> 00:17:42,760
What's gotten into you?

258
00:17:43,600 --> 00:17:45,440
I'm thinking of
organizing a cycling trip.

259
00:17:45,840 --> 00:17:51,800
We have a bicycle café. We should invite
people who are interested to join.

260
00:17:51,840 --> 00:17:53,960
What do you think?

261
00:17:54,000 --> 00:17:57,400
Good idea.
I'll invite customers from my club.

262
00:17:57,400 --> 00:18:00,680
Good. I'll invite my patients to join.

263
00:18:01,120 --> 00:18:04,680
I'm in. I'll invite
customers from the shop.

264
00:18:04,880 --> 00:18:07,800
I'll invite customers from the café.

265
00:18:07,960 --> 00:18:10,520
- Right, Mom?
- Yes, sweetie.

266
00:18:10,640 --> 00:18:12,000
Let's unwrap these.

267
00:18:19,603 --> 00:18:22,230
- Help mom unwrap it.
- Don't take it.

268
00:18:38,440 --> 00:18:39,520
Nava.

269
00:18:42,600 --> 00:18:43,840
How can you come here?

270
00:18:43,840 --> 00:18:45,000
I'm on a break.

271
00:18:45,520 --> 00:18:47,520
I saw your story and decided to drop by.

272
00:18:48,480 --> 00:18:49,640
Are you drunk?

273
00:18:50,360 --> 00:18:51,120
No.

274
00:18:51,680 --> 00:18:52,760
Are you sure?

275
00:18:53,280 --> 00:18:54,320
Not yet.

276
00:18:54,360 --> 00:18:55,520
You sure?!

277
00:18:58,680 --> 00:19:00,560
Wanna go cycling this Saturday?

278
00:19:01,200 --> 00:19:02,280
Cycling?

279
00:19:02,320 --> 00:19:05,440
My family's café is organizing a trip.

280
00:19:08,600 --> 00:19:15,240
I've wanted to go on a trip
but… I never got a chance.

281
00:19:15,880 --> 00:19:17,160
Then come with me.

282
00:19:17,560 --> 00:19:20,000
- Okay.
- Cheers.

283
00:19:25,272 --> 00:19:27,632
If you're free,
please join us on the trip.

284
00:19:27,800 --> 00:19:30,160
Sure thing. Thanks for the invite.

285
00:19:30,160 --> 00:19:31,760
Sounds interesting. Which day?

286
00:19:31,800 --> 00:19:32,880
This Saturday.

287
00:19:33,880 --> 00:19:36,560
It's a chill ride to enjoy the view.

288
00:19:36,600 --> 00:19:38,520
I'll join if I'm free.

289
00:19:44,400 --> 00:19:45,600
Are you guys free?

290
00:19:45,760 --> 00:19:47,080
Make yourselves free for this.

291
00:19:47,280 --> 00:19:49,880
It's the "Heart-Healing Trip."

292
00:19:50,360 --> 00:19:53,760
Over 50 people have signed up.
I'm organizing it.

293
00:19:54,040 --> 00:19:56,120
So, come join us if you can.

294
00:19:56,160 --> 00:19:58,040
That's good. It sounds interesting.

295
00:19:58,080 --> 00:20:02,480
I haven't cycled in ages.
I'll need to warm up.

296
00:20:02,520 --> 00:20:05,320
Alright, are we ready?

297
00:20:05,320 --> 00:20:09,920
If you don't have any plans,
come cycling with us this Saturday.

298
00:20:13,120 --> 00:20:15,160
Do you think you can handle the ride?

299
00:20:19,000 --> 00:20:20,440
Wooh!

300
00:20:29,280 --> 00:20:32,600
Damn, P'Nabnueng!
Tons of people are interested.

301
00:20:32,640 --> 00:20:34,280
Look at all these sign-ups.

302
00:20:34,360 --> 00:20:37,240
- Of course.
- You're the man, bro.

303
00:20:39,040 --> 00:20:42,160
Hey, we haven't
hung out like this in ages.

304
00:20:42,240 --> 00:20:45,240
- Let's have a toast!
- What are we waiting for?!

305
00:20:48,880 --> 00:20:52,680
Hey, bro. About this trip,

306
00:20:52,713 --> 00:20:59,513
you do this to… heal your own heart?

307
00:20:59,680 --> 00:21:05,200
Yeah, you've been looking stressed.
Can you really move on from Yanin?

308
00:21:08,560 --> 00:21:09,560
I can.

309
00:21:09,600 --> 00:21:11,480
What?! With who?! Tell me!

310
00:21:11,480 --> 00:21:12,320
That's quick.

311
00:21:12,800 --> 00:21:13,480
Hey,

312
00:21:14,080 --> 00:21:15,680
does it have to be someone?

313
00:21:15,720 --> 00:21:16,920
I'm working!

314
00:21:17,080 --> 00:21:18,480
Haven't you heard?

315
00:21:19,200 --> 00:21:20,400
"Just focus on work."

316
00:21:20,440 --> 00:21:22,440
- Aww…
- Yeah, work…

317
00:21:22,480 --> 00:21:24,200
- But Looksoh said…
- What?

318
00:21:24,240 --> 00:21:26,200
you went cycling with an American guy.

319
00:21:26,880 --> 00:21:29,560
What guy? No, you're wrong!

320
00:21:32,240 --> 00:21:33,280
Just a kid!

321
00:21:34,600 --> 00:21:35,600
I see…

322
00:21:36,480 --> 00:21:38,320
And who is that kid?

323
00:21:39,000 --> 00:21:40,240
His name is Sailom.

324
00:21:40,520 --> 00:21:41,960
He's just a kid.

325
00:21:42,080 --> 00:21:43,440
But he has…

326
00:21:44,400 --> 00:21:45,120
a condition.

327
00:21:46,200 --> 00:21:48,160
Haphephobia.

328
00:21:48,400 --> 00:21:49,800
You can't touch him like this.

329
00:21:49,880 --> 00:21:51,640
- No touching?
- Yep.

330
00:21:51,680 --> 00:21:52,960
How can you date him?

331
00:21:56,840 --> 00:21:58,720
I need to… treat him first.

332
00:21:59,120 --> 00:22:01,520
Ah, so if you…

333
00:22:02,000 --> 00:22:04,280
If you date him,

334
00:22:04,560 --> 00:22:08,200
do you have to keep your distance
like this when you have sex with him?

335
00:22:10,440 --> 00:22:13,920
That'd hurt like hell if you hit there.
Sorry. Just teasing.

336
00:22:15,960 --> 00:22:17,840
You were so bold.

337
00:22:17,880 --> 00:22:20,080
I know. I was teasing him.

338
00:22:20,240 --> 00:22:21,440
What about you?!

339
00:22:22,000 --> 00:22:24,440
- Look at him deflecting.
- Yeah.

340
00:22:25,720 --> 00:22:28,600
Got someone yet?
You've been awfully quiet lately.

341
00:22:28,960 --> 00:22:31,520
Yeah, What's the deal? Spill it.

342
00:22:33,360 --> 00:22:36,520
I fix bicycles. I don't have time for that.

343
00:22:38,880 --> 00:22:39,840
What about…

344
00:22:40,320 --> 00:22:43,400
your favorite little brother?

345
00:22:44,280 --> 00:22:47,200
Hardly stays home.
Probably gets clingy with a customer.

346
00:22:47,225 --> 00:22:50,385
What? No, I don't have anyone!

347
00:22:50,440 --> 00:22:53,440
I never get attached to customers, bro.

348
00:22:53,480 --> 00:22:55,000
They get attached to me.

349
00:22:55,000 --> 00:22:56,680
Woah!

350
00:22:57,560 --> 00:22:58,720
So cool!

351
00:22:58,760 --> 00:23:01,440
Total Sigma male energy!

352
00:23:03,400 --> 00:23:05,400
Damn, I'm proud of you.

353
00:23:05,840 --> 00:23:06,920
Awesome.

354
00:23:08,840 --> 00:23:09,960
But seriously…

355
00:23:13,200 --> 00:23:15,680
I want to quit being a host.

356
00:23:15,920 --> 00:23:17,120
Quit?

357
00:23:17,560 --> 00:23:18,360
Why?

358
00:23:22,160 --> 00:23:23,320
I feel like...

359
00:23:23,960 --> 00:23:28,440
I'm getting too
emotionally involved lately.

360
00:23:28,480 --> 00:23:31,240
But deep down, in reality...

361
00:23:31,640 --> 00:23:35,240
There's no way we could
ever have a real relationship.

362
00:23:37,920 --> 00:23:39,720
You get what I mean?

363
00:23:40,160 --> 00:23:41,440
Are you even listening?

364
00:23:47,400 --> 00:23:48,680
Oh, come on.

365
00:24:01,240 --> 00:24:03,840
Still better than feeling something
but pretending you don't.

366
00:24:12,480 --> 00:24:14,400
(He's acting weird.)

367
00:24:14,600 --> 00:24:15,800
(Big time.)

368
00:24:21,400 --> 00:24:23,080
The hell is weird? Cheers!

369
00:24:24,360 --> 00:24:27,040
Nice dodge.
I'll let it slide for now.

370
00:24:32,640 --> 00:24:34,360
Are you serious about quitting?

371
00:24:34,440 --> 00:24:36,000
Of course!

372
00:24:36,000 --> 00:24:38,160
- He's just drunk.
- Hey, bro!

373
00:24:38,200 --> 00:24:40,680
The money is great, but…

374
00:24:41,080 --> 00:24:43,040
I don't want to do this forever.

375
00:24:43,720 --> 00:24:46,920
Obsessed with a customer, for sure.

376
00:24:47,266 --> 00:24:51,826
My ass! I'm not attached to them.
They're attached to me.

377
00:24:58,080 --> 00:25:01,920
(Bring your friends along too.)

378
00:25:04,080 --> 00:25:05,880
(Sure thing, P'Doc.)

379
00:25:06,960 --> 00:25:10,000
Wow, look at that grin.

380
00:25:10,040 --> 00:25:12,040
Is it your P'Doc again?

381
00:25:12,360 --> 00:25:16,720
Yeah, you're so nosy.
Anyway, come cycling with me.

382
00:25:17,280 --> 00:25:18,360
Cycling?

383
00:25:18,680 --> 00:25:19,640
Yep.

384
00:25:20,280 --> 00:25:22,720
It's the P'Doc's cycling trip.

385
00:25:23,000 --> 00:25:24,760
I already signed you up.

386
00:25:25,920 --> 00:25:29,280
Are you kidding?
Do I look like a cyclist?

387
00:25:29,320 --> 00:25:30,920
Guys, give me a hand.

388
00:25:35,520 --> 00:25:37,240
Why did you buy so much stuff?

389
00:25:37,680 --> 00:25:39,760
Oh, like you eat any less.

390
00:25:39,800 --> 00:25:43,440
We're eating at home for your safety.
So, you don't have to bump into anyone.

391
00:25:44,200 --> 00:25:45,280
What about the ice?

392
00:25:45,280 --> 00:25:46,400
Go get it yourself.

393
00:25:46,440 --> 00:25:48,120
Hey, I'm playing a game now.

394
00:25:48,560 --> 00:25:49,960
Look at this guy!

395
00:25:50,120 --> 00:25:52,800
- I'm chatting with P'Doc.
- I'm playing my game.

396
00:25:57,840 --> 00:26:00,720
Cheers! Yay!

397
00:26:08,200 --> 00:26:10,480
So, Sailom...

398
00:26:10,800 --> 00:26:12,400
have you slept with him yet?

399
00:26:12,600 --> 00:26:13,720
Are you crazy?!

400
00:26:14,366 --> 00:26:18,206
When would I even have the chance?
Look at my condition.

401
00:26:18,320 --> 00:26:23,320
Did you think about that if you weren't like
this, you might've already been his boyfriend?

402
00:26:26,720 --> 00:26:27,800
I have.

403
00:26:29,240 --> 00:26:31,880
But I don't know how
he feels about me.

404
00:26:33,080 --> 00:26:35,520
Why don't you just ask him out directly?

405
00:26:37,280 --> 00:26:39,520
If he doesn't feel the same,

406
00:26:40,160 --> 00:26:41,680
I'll just look like a fool.

407
00:26:42,200 --> 00:26:43,120
True.

408
00:26:44,040 --> 00:26:47,200
But I think you need to get cured first.

409
00:26:47,640 --> 00:26:52,800
Otherwise, you won't be happy
even if you date him. Right?

410
00:26:54,080 --> 00:26:57,640
Yeah. If you can't touch each other,
how's it gonna work?

411
00:26:58,160 --> 00:27:01,720
- How are you guys gonna have sex?
- What the hell are you talking about?!

412
00:27:01,720 --> 00:27:03,720
Am I lying, though?

413
00:27:07,560 --> 00:27:08,520
Fine.

414
00:27:09,280 --> 00:27:12,440
How am I supposed to get cured?

415
00:27:13,560 --> 00:27:17,520
Didn't you tell me he's a psychiatrist?

416
00:27:17,520 --> 00:27:21,360
Get the treatment and get the guy.

417
00:27:22,640 --> 00:27:24,000
Good point.

418
00:27:25,880 --> 00:27:27,840
Hey, you guys...

419
00:27:29,640 --> 00:27:30,960
Cheers!

420
00:27:31,000 --> 00:27:33,360
- Cheers!
- Yay!

421
00:28:13,000 --> 00:28:13,960
Sailom?!

422
00:28:22,320 --> 00:28:23,840
What are you doing here?

423
00:29:19,720 --> 00:29:20,680
Sailom.

424
00:29:21,400 --> 00:29:22,520
Sailom…

425
00:29:28,920 --> 00:29:29,840
Sailom!

426
00:29:32,880 --> 00:29:33,680
Yes?!

427
00:29:34,800 --> 00:29:36,240
Are you daydreaming?

428
00:29:36,880 --> 00:29:38,560
You even did a 'kiss-kiss' face.

429
00:29:39,800 --> 00:29:42,440
I was thinking about eating strawberries.

430
00:29:42,720 --> 00:29:43,880
Strawberries.

431
00:29:43,920 --> 00:29:45,040
Kiss-kiss.

432
00:29:47,640 --> 00:29:49,640
Shall we get started?

433
00:29:52,160 --> 00:29:54,680
What made you decide
to seek treatment with me?

434
00:29:56,520 --> 00:29:58,320
My friends hyped me up.

435
00:29:59,320 --> 00:30:02,400
And I really want to get
cured of this condition.

436
00:30:05,206 --> 00:30:07,606
I know it won't be easy,

437
00:30:08,080 --> 00:30:09,560
and I'm scared.

438
00:30:10,920 --> 00:30:11,760
But...

439
00:30:12,313 --> 00:30:14,473
I don't want to feel this way anymore.

440
00:30:15,760 --> 00:30:17,920
And what about the cycling trip?

441
00:30:18,760 --> 00:30:20,280
Have you invited your friends yet?

442
00:30:21,160 --> 00:30:22,280
I have.

443
00:30:22,960 --> 00:30:25,320
Lemon and James are dying to join.

444
00:30:25,680 --> 00:30:30,240
We're already looking for
a place to practice our riding.

445
00:30:31,160 --> 00:30:34,000
Great. You won't get
too tired on the big day.

446
00:30:34,720 --> 00:30:37,320
It's going to be very sunny that day.

447
00:30:41,280 --> 00:30:44,400
Don't forget to wear sunscreen,
so you don't get burned.

448
00:30:44,600 --> 00:30:46,320
This is for you.

449
00:30:48,280 --> 00:30:49,280
Thanks.

450
00:30:49,880 --> 00:30:52,680
So, what did you do today?
Tell me about it.

451
00:30:53,560 --> 00:30:55,960
Nothing much, really.

452
00:30:57,240 --> 00:31:01,280
Oh, seeing you is the
highlight of my day.

453
00:31:03,400 --> 00:31:07,480
Uh... I mean, because
I don't get to visit the clinic often.

454
00:31:13,120 --> 00:31:13,920
Sailom.

455
00:31:15,240 --> 00:31:15,960
Yes?

456
00:31:24,120 --> 00:31:25,880
Hello, Mr. Sailom.

457
00:31:26,640 --> 00:31:32,960
I'm Doctor Ying. I'll be taking over
your case from today on.

458
00:31:34,640 --> 00:31:35,520
Right…

459
00:31:36,320 --> 00:31:38,080
How are you doing today?

460
00:31:40,280 --> 00:31:41,320
I'm fine...

461
00:31:41,800 --> 00:31:45,680
And... did you sleep well last night?

462
00:31:47,200 --> 00:31:48,200
Pretty good...

463
00:31:48,840 --> 00:31:52,160
What did you have
for breakfast this morning?

464
00:31:54,400 --> 00:31:56,360
Just some coffee and a sandwich.

465
00:31:56,800 --> 00:31:57,680
I see.

466
00:31:59,760 --> 00:32:03,760
According to your records,
you're studying abroad, right?

467
00:32:06,360 --> 00:32:07,440
Yes...

468
00:32:08,240 --> 00:32:09,800
I'm studying in the States.

469
00:32:11,320 --> 00:32:13,960
It's summer break now,
so I'm back to stay with my dad.

470
00:32:15,200 --> 00:32:16,840
Staying with your father?

471
00:32:19,073 --> 00:32:22,073
So, are you originally from Pattaya?

472
00:32:23,640 --> 00:32:24,840
Sailom…

473
00:32:27,200 --> 00:32:30,200
- This is our new home, sweetie.
- Yes, Mom.

474
00:32:30,240 --> 00:32:32,840
Oh, you're finally here.

475
00:32:36,240 --> 00:32:37,640
Say hello to him, dear.

476
00:32:38,080 --> 00:32:39,200
Hello, sir.

477
00:32:39,320 --> 00:32:40,720
Welcome home, son.

478
00:32:41,080 --> 00:32:44,240
From now on, we're one big family.

479
00:32:44,600 --> 00:32:45,680
Yes, sir.

480
00:32:54,960 --> 00:32:56,280
Eat up, son.

481
00:32:58,080 --> 00:32:59,960
So you can grow up strong.

482
00:33:14,880 --> 00:33:17,440
You can always tell me
if you have problems.

483
00:33:53,760 --> 00:33:55,960
Don't you dare tell anyone about this.

484
00:33:56,880 --> 00:33:59,360
Or I'll kill your mother.

485
00:36:09,320 --> 00:36:11,280
You're quite good at hiding.

486
00:36:15,200 --> 00:36:17,120
If I catch you...

487
00:36:18,120 --> 00:36:20,560
you're going to be punished, son.

488
00:36:26,400 --> 00:36:28,760
Could you be right...

489
00:37:02,520 --> 00:37:03,720
HERE?!

490
00:37:03,920 --> 00:37:05,040
There you are!

491
00:37:05,200 --> 00:37:10,400
- Don't squirm! Come on! Get out!
- Let me go! Let go of me!

492
00:37:16,120 --> 00:37:16,840
Ying…

493
00:37:18,200 --> 00:37:19,200
where's Sailom?

494
00:37:19,800 --> 00:37:21,800
He left a little while ago.

495
00:37:24,040 --> 00:37:25,560
Look...

496
00:37:25,840 --> 00:37:27,760
he doesn't seem ready at all.

497
00:37:32,160 --> 00:37:34,800
Is something bothering you? Or...

498
00:37:35,280 --> 00:37:37,080
do you want to take over this case?

499
00:37:37,200 --> 00:37:41,640
No, don't worry about it.
I asked for your help with this one.

500
00:37:41,800 --> 00:37:43,600
It's best if you handle it.

501
00:37:51,240 --> 00:37:55,280
Oh, I have an errand to run. Gotta go.

502
00:37:55,880 --> 00:37:57,080
See you later.

503
00:38:20,240 --> 00:38:21,240
Hello?

504
00:38:21,640 --> 00:38:22,760
Phailin?

505
00:38:23,280 --> 00:38:24,600
This is Lada.

506
00:38:27,080 --> 00:38:28,920
How is Nabnueng doing?

507
00:38:33,040 --> 00:38:34,400
You've got the wrong number.

508
00:39:28,120 --> 00:39:29,360
Were you sleeping?

509
00:39:32,320 --> 00:39:34,040
Sleeping on the job, are you?

510
00:39:35,280 --> 00:39:36,960
Just resting my eyes.

511
00:39:37,760 --> 00:39:40,720
The cookies need to
cool down before getting packed.

512
00:39:41,480 --> 00:39:43,600
Do you even know
anything about baking?

513
00:39:44,120 --> 00:39:45,360
You were asleep.

514
00:39:51,000 --> 00:39:52,800
Yeah, I was.

515
00:39:53,560 --> 00:39:54,640
So what?

516
00:39:55,760 --> 00:39:57,040
That's it.

517
00:39:58,000 --> 00:39:59,640
I hired you,

518
00:40:00,200 --> 00:40:02,120
but you're sleeping during working hours?!

519
00:40:03,200 --> 00:40:04,920
I'm docking your pay.

520
00:40:05,360 --> 00:40:07,640
You're a terrible
example for the others.

521
00:40:09,520 --> 00:40:11,360
Whoa, whoa. Hey…

522
00:40:11,880 --> 00:40:13,440
Calm down, man.

523
00:40:13,920 --> 00:40:16,760
Calm down? You're sleeping.

524
00:40:17,120 --> 00:40:18,640
You can punch me.

525
00:40:18,920 --> 00:40:20,720
Just don't touch my salary.

526
00:40:21,160 --> 00:40:23,240
I don't even have enough to get by.

527
00:40:24,640 --> 00:40:28,000
Hit me. Just hit me. Right here.

528
00:40:28,880 --> 00:40:30,280
Then we'll be even.

529
00:40:30,400 --> 00:40:34,360
- Let go of me!
- I said punch me!

530
00:40:36,480 --> 00:40:39,080
Just don't touch my salary!

531
00:41:15,160 --> 00:41:16,480
P'Dindin,

532
00:41:20,360 --> 00:41:21,600
are you okay?

533
00:41:24,240 --> 00:41:25,440
I'm fine.

534
00:41:25,440 --> 00:41:28,760
Take it easy. Don't take
P'Tawan's words too seriously.

535
00:41:28,800 --> 00:41:31,960
He won't actually cut
your pay. It's an empty threat.

536
00:41:32,000 --> 00:41:35,200
He's got a sharp tongue,
but a kind heart. Right, Mickey?

537
00:41:35,600 --> 00:41:39,760
Yeah, that's just how he is.
Don't stress out, P'Dindin.

538
00:42:06,160 --> 00:42:08,360
- Hello, P'Man.
- Hey.

539
00:42:13,000 --> 00:42:15,400
- Let's have a drink.
- Alright.

540
00:42:18,360 --> 00:42:19,560
I'll pour it for you.

541
00:42:19,560 --> 00:42:22,680
It's okay. I'll do it myself.

542
00:42:26,200 --> 00:42:27,160
Here's yours.

543
00:42:29,320 --> 00:42:30,640
You like it strong.

544
00:42:32,760 --> 00:42:34,040
Cheers.

545
00:42:37,600 --> 00:42:40,560
I thought you wouldn't come.
I saw you were taking a break.

546
00:42:40,920 --> 00:42:45,560
You booked me for the whole night.
Of course, I had to come.

547
00:42:47,120 --> 00:42:50,640
I missed you, Sky.
Come stay at my place tonight.

548
00:42:50,960 --> 00:42:55,320
Whoa, P'Man.
You're not gonna let me go home?

549
00:42:55,686 --> 00:43:00,566
What? You've stayed over before.
Why do you want to go home?

550
00:43:04,560 --> 00:43:06,600
- It's just...
- Why?

551
00:43:07,240 --> 00:43:09,200
You don't want to be with me anymore?

552
00:43:10,440 --> 00:43:11,960
It's not like that...

553
00:43:12,000 --> 00:43:15,120
Of course, you don't want to.

554
00:43:15,120 --> 00:43:18,360
If I didn't care about you,
why would I be here all night?

555
00:43:18,400 --> 00:43:20,040
Cheers to that.

556
00:43:29,600 --> 00:43:30,480
Sky...

557
00:43:31,600 --> 00:43:32,920
I thought you were taking a break.

558
00:43:34,520 --> 00:43:35,640
Nava...

559
00:43:38,360 --> 00:43:40,280
P'Man booked me for the whole night.

560
00:43:42,800 --> 00:43:45,200
Can I help you? This is my table.

561
00:43:46,800 --> 00:43:49,480
My bad. I'm here say hi to Sky.

562
00:43:50,360 --> 00:43:53,600
Where are your manners?!
I paid for his time tonight!

563
00:43:54,720 --> 00:43:55,760
So?

564
00:43:56,280 --> 00:43:58,960
I can't say hi to my friend?

565
00:44:00,240 --> 00:44:01,720
Are you looking for trouble?

566
00:44:02,480 --> 00:44:03,480
No, I'm not.

567
00:44:05,400 --> 00:44:09,120
When you booked him,
did I ever get in your way?!

568
00:44:12,680 --> 00:44:13,640
Sky,

569
00:44:14,160 --> 00:44:16,480
- is that your glass?
- Yeah.

570
00:44:28,240 --> 00:44:29,320
That's enough!

571
00:44:33,120 --> 00:44:34,640
Hey! Nava, stop!

572
00:44:35,560 --> 00:44:37,600
I said stop!

573
00:44:38,600 --> 00:44:39,680
STOP!!

574
00:44:42,400 --> 00:44:44,240
P'Man, please calm down.

575
00:44:45,240 --> 00:44:46,240
Let's go, Nava.

576
00:44:46,280 --> 00:44:47,320
Where are you going?!

577
00:44:47,760 --> 00:44:50,000
Stay with me! Let him go!

578
00:44:51,320 --> 00:44:52,640
Hey, stop!

579
00:44:52,680 --> 00:44:53,480
Ah!

580
00:44:54,920 --> 00:44:55,680
Mr. Man!

581
00:44:55,680 --> 00:44:57,880
Security! Get him out of here! Now!

582
00:44:57,920 --> 00:44:59,360
Please calm down, Mr. Man.

583
00:44:59,880 --> 00:45:01,320
- We're so sorry.
- I'm so sorry, Mama.

584
00:45:01,320 --> 00:45:02,480
Take care of him.

585
00:45:02,520 --> 00:45:03,840
P'Man, take it easy.

586
00:45:03,840 --> 00:45:07,040
Did you see him?!
He was trying to screw with me!

587
00:45:07,520 --> 00:45:09,240
Why didn't you stand up for me?!

588
00:45:09,720 --> 00:45:12,080
Look at me. I'm right here with you.

589
00:45:12,720 --> 00:45:15,360
Please calm down.
Let's go back and have fun.

590
00:45:15,360 --> 00:45:17,240
Hey! Nothing to see here!
Keep the party going!

591
00:45:17,280 --> 00:45:20,480
Let's just go back and have fun, okay?

592
00:45:21,480 --> 00:45:23,280
Let me fill your glass.

593
00:45:23,920 --> 00:45:26,760
I'll even go back to your room tonight.

594
00:45:26,800 --> 00:45:30,040
You're out of drinks.
Let me get you another one.

595
00:45:31,200 --> 00:45:32,080
Hey!

596
00:46:44,120 --> 00:46:46,108
(Next Episode)
What the hell do you want from me now?!

597
00:46:46,133 --> 00:46:47,360
Someone to drink with

598
00:46:47,480 --> 00:46:48,440
I'm not drinking.

599
00:46:48,560 --> 00:46:54,040
Tawan might act tough on the outside,
but he's actually a very kind person.

600
00:46:54,880 --> 00:46:57,440
- I'm thinking about quitting the host job.
- Why?

601
00:46:59,560 --> 00:47:01,680
What's wrong?
You've been spacing out all morning.

602
00:47:01,800 --> 00:47:04,280
Can you tell me what's going on?

603
00:47:04,360 --> 00:47:06,480
Why did you decide to stop the treatment?

604
00:47:06,520 --> 00:47:09,520
If this treatment is like
riding a bike, just like you said.

605
00:47:09,600 --> 00:47:12,600
Now, you've cycled
far away and left me behind.

